New York Mets Reinstate Outfielder Angel Pagan From 15-Day Disabled List

-- B y   M a s o n   L e v i n s o n
-- 
2011-05-27T20:16:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/new-york-mets-reinstate-outfielder-angel-pagan-from-15-day-disabled-list.html
New York Mets outfielder Angel Pagan
was reinstated from the 15-day disabled list, the Mets said in a
news release.  The team also selected the contract of right-handed pitcher
Dale Thayer from Triple-A Buffalo, designated left-hander Pat
Misch for assignment and optioned outfielder Fernando Martinez
to Buffalo.  Pagan, 29, strained his left oblique on April 21. He was
hitting .159 in 19 games prior to the injury.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mason Levinson at 
 mlevinson@bloomberg.net  